s life-long and relapses can occur. Initial dosages of 5-10 mg/kg/day of elemental zinc, followed by maintenance doses of 1-2 mg/kg/day are recommended and are taken orally. Zinc sulphate is the best tolerated preparation, in most cases, but it can also be administered as acetate, gluconate and amino acid chelates. Zinc and copper levels should be monitored regularly. Dosages need to be increased during periods of growth, such as adolescence and during pregnancy, when relapses can occur.", "prognosis": "With adherence to life-long zinc substitution therapy, the prognosis is good. Only when infants are left untreated can the disease be fatal."}, {"name": "AFAP", "sub_name": "Polyposis , adenomat\u00f6se attenuierte famili\u00e4re", "english": 0, "defenition": "Eine milde Form der famili\u00e4ren adenomat\u00f6sen Polyposis, die durch das Vorhandensein von weniger als 100 adenomat\u00f6sen Kolonpolypen, eine proximalere Kolonlokalisation, ein verz\u00f6gertes Alter f\u00fcr das Auftreten von Darmkrebs und eine begrenztere Auspr\u00e4gung der extrakolonischen Merkmale gekennzeichnet ist.", "synonyms": "AFAP, FAP, attenuierte, Polyposis coli, attenuierte famili\u00e4re, ", "inheritance": "Autosomal-dominant\u00a0oder\u00a0Autosomal-rezessiv\u00a0", "age_of_onset": "Erwachsenenalter", "ICD-10": "D12.6", "OMIM": "175100\u00a0 608456\u00a0 612591\u00a0 615083\u00a0 616415", "UMLS": "C2674616", "MeSH": "C538265", "GARD": "8532"}, {"name": "AFH", "sub_name": "Histiozytom, angiomat\u00f6ses fibr\u00f6ses", "german_description": "Eine Kurzbeschreibung der Krankheit wird derzeit erstellt. Weiterf\u00fchrende Informationen zu dieser Krankheit k\u00f6nnen \u00fcber das Menu  am unteren Bildrand abgerufen werden.", "english": 1, "defenition": "A rare soft tissue tumor characterized by a slow-growing, usually painless, subcutaneous nodule, predominantly located in the extremities, less frequently the trunk or head and neck region. Histopathologically, the lesion is well-circumscrib