erotaxy and digit anomalies.", "genetic_counseling": "Transmission is autosomal recessive. Genetic counseling should be offered to at-risk couples (both individuals are carriers of a disease-causing mutation) informing them of the 25% risk of having an affected child at each pregnancy. Phenotypic expression varies considerably, even within the same family. Genetic counseling is recommended to affected families.", "management_and_treatment": "Multidisciplinary management and treatment is required. Most patients with this syndrome will undergo early craniofacial reconstruction to improve appearance and prevent intellectual disability. Surgery may be required for congenital heart defects and shunting may be required if there is raised intercranial pressure.", "prognosis": "The prognosis is highly variable depending on the severity of the malformations and the degree of intellectual disability; some children grow up to become independent adults and others require more support due to intellectual disability or physical challenges. Life expectancy is shortened, mainly due to heart defects."}, {"name": "Akrozephalopolysyndaktylie Typ 4", "sub_name": "Goodman-Syndrom", "german_description": "Das Goodman-Syndrom ist eine au\u00dferordentlich seltene genetische Krankheit mit ausgepr\u00e4gten Fehlbildungen des Kopfes und Gesichtes (letztlich im Sinne einer Akrozephalie), Anomalien der H\u00e4nde und F\u00fc\u00dfe (Polydaktylie, Syndaktylie, Klinodaktylie, ulnare Abweichung der Finger) und angeborenem Herzfehler. Das Syndrom wird autosomal-rezessiv vererbt. Einige Autoren halten das Goodman-Syndrom f\u00fcr eine Variante des Carpenter-Syndroms (Akrozephalopolysyndaktylie Typ II). ", "english": 1, "defenition": "A rare syndromic trigonocephaly characterized by marked malformations of the head and face (essentially acrocephaly), broad depressed nasal bridge, narrow maxillae, abnormalities of the hands and feet (polydactyly, brachydactyly, syndactyly, clinodactyly, camptodactyly